<heading>bg - Resume a background flow.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  bg
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Brings a suspended background flow to the foreground.

A flow started with start_cmd or start_task may go into the
background when its job is suspended.  bg resumes it to the
current foreground slot.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
jobs, stop, fg, man
</paragraph>
